The IDE already saved the JS changes. The fix is in place. Here's a summary of what changed and why it works:

---

## What changed

**Reverted** `mylearningbanner.html` — the `<li>` is back to showing all breadcrumb items with no filter.

**Added** to `mylearningbanner.js` (lines 3–12):
```javascript
var bcItems = document.querySelectorAll('.mylearning .dds__breadcrumb__item');
for (var i = 1; i < bcItems.length; i++) {
    var prevLink = bcItems[i - 1].querySelector('a');
    var currLink = bcItems[i].querySelector('a');
    if (prevLink && currLink && prevLink.href === currLink.href) {
        bcItems[i].remove();
    }
}
```

---

## Why this is better

The HTL fix `navItemList.first || navItemList.last` was a blunt rule — it blindly removed every middle item regardless of what it was. That's why it broke Help/Certification Issues (removing "Help", which is a meaningful item).

The JS fix is smarter — it only removes an item when its **href matches the previous item's href**. So:

| Page | Breadcrumb items | Prev href == Curr href? | Result |
|---|---|---|---|
| My Training | Home / NavTitle / My Training | Home ≡ NavTitle ✅ remove | homeIcon / My Training |
| Help / Cert Issues | Home / Help / Cert Issues | Home ≠ Help ❌ keep | homeIcon / Help / Cert Issues |
